## Pipeline Retro: openai-rust — 7.7/10

**5 runs, 6 tracks, 26 iterations, 183 minutes total**

### Top 3 Failure Patterns

1. **Deploy AskUserQuestion (CRITICAL)** — 7 wasted iters in runs 1-2. Crate name conflict triggered interactive questions in headless pipeline mode. 3rd project with this defect.
2. **Redo loops** — 3 cycles, but all productive (real fixes). Redo limit (2) worked correctly.
3. **Deploy signal gap** — self-resolved once naming was sorted. Runs 3-5 were zero-waste.

### Key Numbers

| Metric | Value |
|--------|-------|
| Tests | 151 pass, 0 fail |
| Commits | 77 (98.7% conventional) |
| Published | openai-oxide v0.5.0 on crates.io |
| Waste trend | 50% → 67% → 20% → 0% → 0% |
| Plan fidelity | 100% criteria met across all tracks |

### Top 3 Recommendations

1. **[CRITICAL]** Fix deploy skill — suppress `AskUserQuestion` when `$SOLO_PIPELINE=1`, auto-resolve from `Cargo.toml`
2. **[HIGH]** Add Rust/crate publish strategy to deploy skill (currently web-app biased)
3. **[MEDIUM]** `/plan` should detect overlapping plans and consolidate

### What Worked Best

- Python SDK local-read workflow → 100% field coverage
- Auto-plan picked up 2 additional tracks from backlog, both zero-waste
- Progressive delivery: 6 crates.io releases (v0.1.0 → v0.5.0)
- Runs 3-5: 11 iterations, 0 waste

